This paper deals with privacy and security concerns related to the release of high-fidelity energy networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of Differential Privacy (DP), which is a popular technique in machine learning and data privacy research, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another likely category. The paper presents a novel differential privacy mechanism, which involves designing algorithms and models, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category. The paper also discusses the experimental results, which involve data analysis and visualization, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves the use of mathematical models and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible category.
